cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper deals with database encryption schemes and their security implications, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses privacy and confidentiality, which are important topics in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The application of the encryption schemes to privacy policy audits involves analyzing logs, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper presents algorithms and security definitions, which could be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
